</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA12d233n2-ptr" id="PJA12d233n2">2</a>
<p>Pieter van Bleiswyck.</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA12d233n3-ptr" id="PJA12d233n3">3</a>
<p>See Art. 1 of the <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-11-02-0306-0002" class="document">Austro-Russian Proposal for Anglo-American Peace Negotiations</a> (vol. 11:408410).</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA12d233n4-ptr" id="PJA12d233n4">4</a>
<p>A reference to Shakespeare, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">The Tempest</span>, Act I, scene ii, lines 274279. This was one of <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s favorite literary allusions, and one that he consistently got wrong: Ariel was imprisoned in a cloven pine. See, for example, vol. 8:<a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-08-02-0104" class="document">145</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-08-02-0158" class="document">224</a>.</p>
